%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-driving-worth-it-low-tips-rare-minimum-wage-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eride-hailing%20driver%3C%2Fa%3E%20Lee%20Sperry%20has%20spent%20the%20last%20year%20pushing%20for%20better%20treatment%20from%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20advocacy%20group%20San%20Diego%20Drivers%20United.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20lately%2C%20he's%20asking%3A%20Why%20not%20create%20something%20that%20drivers%20could%20use%20instead%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-product-manager-ai-use-at-work-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Lyft%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESperry%20and%20several%20hundred%20fellow%20drivers%20in%20San%20Diego%20are%20exploring%20forming%20a%20cooperative.%20Instead%20of%20driving%20for%20the%20established%20apps%2C%20Sperry%20said%2C%20they%20would%20set%20up%20their%20own%20app%2C%20elect%20leaders%20to%20manage%20it%2C%20and%20create%20transparent%20policies%20around%20issues%20such%20as%20deactivating%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20co-op%20would%20be%20very%20different%20in%20the%20way%20it%20operates%2C%20in%20the%20way%20that%20we%20handle%20how%20the%20app%20works%20and%20how%20the%20pricing%20goes%2C%20how%20the%20driver%20gets%20paid%2C%20how%20the%20hiring%20goes%2C%20who%20makes%20the%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20ride-hailing%20drivers%20are%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20make%20money%20outside%20the%20apps%20as%20their%20earnings%20fall%20and%20claiming%20rides%20gets%20harder.%20Some%20have%20created%20their%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-drivers-starting-own-ride-businesses-as-earnings-drop-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblack-car%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%2C%20like%20Sperry%2C%20are%20creating%20these%20ride-hailing%20cooperatives%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20model%20that%20they%20say%20could%20yield%20better%20returns%20for%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cities%2C%20driver%20co-ops%20already%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20York%20City%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdriver-owned-rideshare-service-new-york-city-review-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Drivers%20Cooperative%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20offering%20rides%20since%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%2C%20Drivers%20Co-op%20Colorado%2C%20launched%20last%20September.%20The%20co-op%20has%20about%2016%2C000%20drivers%2C%20and%20it%20guarantees%20them%2080%25%20of%20each%20fare%20that%20riders%20pay.%20Many%20ride-hailing%20drivers%20say%20they%20get%20paid%20less%20than%20half%20of%20the%20fare%20on%20other%20apps.%20The%20co-op's%20promise%20also%20represents%20a%20greater%20share%20than%20Lyft%2C%20which%20says%20it%20pays%20drivers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flyft-earnings-gig-driver-rider-payments-uber-hourly-pay-stock-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E70%25%20of%20the%20weekly%20rider%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20earn%20after%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhred%20Riggs%2C%20one%20of%20the%20co-op's%20drivers%2C%20said%20that%20he%20has%20seen%20his%20pay%20decline%20for%20the%20same%20rides%20on%20Uber%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20ride%20between%20downtown%20Denver%20and%20Denver%20International%20Airport%20%E2%80%94%20a%20trip%20of%20about%2021%20miles%20that%20takes%20about%2030%20minutes%20with%20light%20traffic%20%E2%80%94%20used%20to%20pay%20drivers%20about%20%2435%2C%20he%20said.%20These%20days%2C%20the%20same%20journey%20grosses%20about%20%2416.%20Through%20the%20co-op's%20set%20prices%2C%20which%20don't%20surge%20based%20on%20demand%2C%20a%20driver%20can%20earn%20%2433.60%20for%20the%20same%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20start%20driving%20for%20the%20co-op%2C%20Riggs%20and%20other%20drivers%20had%20to%20undergo%20a%20background%20check%2C%20a%20requirement%20that%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20also%20have.%20Unlike%20the%20big%20apps%2C%20though%2C%20the%20co-op%20also%20requires%20potential%20drivers%20to%20attend%20an%20orientation%20session.%20They%20also%20have%20the%20option%20to%20buy%20a%20stake%20in%20the%20co-op%20for%20%24200.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20co-op%20requires%20drivers%20to%20use%20dash%20cams%2C%20which%20can%20provide%20evidence%20in%20case%20either%20a%20passenger%20or%20driver%20claims%20that%20something%20bad%20happened%20during%20a%20ride.%20It%20has%20a%20committee%20to%20review%20those%20cases%20and%20decide%20whether%20to%20issue%20a%20warning%20or%20dismiss%20the%20driver%20from%20its%20app%2C%20said%20Isaac%20Chinyoka%2C%20the%20co-op's%20general%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%2C%20Lyft%2C%20and%20other%20gig%20work%20apps%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-gig-workers-are-fighting-against-sudden-account-deactivations-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeactivate%20drivers'%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20providing%20a%20clear%20justification%20or%20a%20transparent%20investigation.%20Some%20drivers%20have%20told%20BI%20that%20following%20up%20with%20the%20companies%20or%20requesting%20arbitration%20to%20get%20their%20accounts%20reactivated%20can%20be%20a%20complicated%20process%2C%20especially%20without%20being%20able%20to%20talk%20to%20someone%20face-to-face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20co-op%20has%20a%20physical%20office%20in%20Denver%20where%20drivers%20can%20speak%20face-to-face%20with%20leadership%2C%20Chinyoka%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20just%20take%20off%20the%20driver%20immediately%20without%20going%20through%20that%20due%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe%20sit%20down%20with%20the%20driver.%20They%20know.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELyft%20told%20BI%20that%20its%20drivers%20can%20take%20on%20other%20employment%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bservices%20similar%20to%20rideshare%20services%20to%20other%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20under%20its%20terms%20of%20service%20for%20independent%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDrivers%20are%20independent%20contractors%20and%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20work%20however%20and%20whenever%20they%20want%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20by%20driving%20for%20other%20ride-share%20platforms%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Uber%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuis%20Arias%2C%20a%20ride-hailing%20driver%20and%20another%20member%20of%20San%20Diego%20Drivers%20United%2C%20said%20that%20he%20hopes%20a%20co-op%20would%20be%20able%20to%20tackle%20a%20variety%20of%20issues%20beyond%20pay%2C%20such%20as%20combating%20drivers%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-spark-delivery-accounts-go-for-hundreds-dollars-social-media-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuy%20and%20use%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20other%20peoples'%20names%20to%20offer%20rides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20about%20how%20bad%20we're%20getting%20screwed%20about%20the%20pay%20rates%2C%20but%20now%20it%20is%20a%20safety%20concern%20issue%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20Uber%2C%20Lyft%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20Instacart%2C%20or%20another%20company%20as%20a%20gig%20worker%20and%20have%20a%20story%20idea%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20abitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-drivers-joining-making-apps-cooperatives-rideshare-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739787422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ae536f6630eb10385c9504%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-drivers-joining-making-apps-cooperatives-rideshare-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ride-hailing%20drivers%20for%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20are%20forming%20cooperatives%20as%20many%20try%20to%20increase%20their%20earnings%20and%20fight%20for%20transparency.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lyft-drivers-joining-making-apps-cooperatives-rideshare-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%224%20trades%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20higher-for-longer%20interest%20rates%20with%20the%20Fed%20not%20expected%20to%20cut%20until%20at%20least%20September%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223580%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679970ab7bb3f854015aef32%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222386%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20Wong%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInflation%20remains%20elevated%2C%20meaning%20the%20Fed%20isn't%20likely%20to%20cut%20rates%20soon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20inflation%20stays%20unchecked%2C%20rate%20hikes%20might%20become%20a%20possibility%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20investing%20experts%20are%20navigating%20a%20higher-for-longer%20interest-rate%20environment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-january-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJanuary%20CPI%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20inflation%20was%20running%20hot%20at%203%25%20year%20over%20year%2C%20Wall%20Street%20was%20already%20bracing%20for%20higher-for-longer%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20inflation%20numbers%20likely%20only%20confirmed%20the%20belief%20of%20many%20investors%20and%20strategists%20that%20rate%20cuts%20are%20off%20the%20table%20until%20at%20least%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20Fed%20cuts%20interest%20rates%20too%20early%2C%20it%20increases%20the%20likelihood%20that%20we%20will%20see%20a%20repeat%20of%20the%201970s.%20The%20Fed%20has%20no%20other%20options%20than%20to%20keep%20interest%20rates%20higher%20for%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20Torsten%20Sl%C3%B8k%2C%20Apollo's%20chief%20economist%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20note.%20The%201970s%20were%20marked%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fuse.insider.com%2Fstory%2F66685af4e7e1e0003ff21db0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estagflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20partly%20due%20to%20the%20Fed%20keeping%20interest%20rates%20too%20low%20for%20too%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20equity%20investors%20might%20wish%20for%20lower%20interest%20rates%2C%20there%20are%20certain%20benefits%20to%20a%20higher-for-longer%20environment%2C%20according%20to%20Michael%20Rosner%2C%20managing%20director%20and%20private%20wealth%20advisor%20at%20Raymond%20James.%20Higher%20rates%20bring%20increased%20opportunities%20in%20fixed%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20anybody%20who%20wants%20to%20put%20money%20outside%20of%20the%20equity%20markets%2C%20higher%20for%20longer%20is%20a%20really%20good%20environment%20for%20that.%20High-yield%20savings%20accounts%2C%20money%20market%20accounts%2C%20CDs%2C%20even%20high-grade%20corporate%20bonds%20are%20paying%20a%20really%20attractive%20rate%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosner%20told%20BI.%20Savers%20or%20anyone%20with%20cash%20on%20the%20sidelines%20will%20benefit%20from%20higher%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Zaccarelli%2C%20chief%20investment%20of%20Northlight%20Asset%20Management%2C%20recommends%3Cstrong%3E%20shorter-duration%20bonds%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20That's%20because%20bonds%20with%20a%20shorter%20duration%20are%20less%20exposed%20to%20interest%20rate%20risk%20and%20also%20offer%20attractive%20yields%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20go%20as%20far%20out%20the%20curve%20to%2010-year%2C%2020-year%2C%2030-year%20bonds%20or%20Treasurys%20in%20order%20to%20get%20higher%20yields.%20You%20can%20get%20quite%20a%20bit%20of%20yield%20in%20the%20shorter%20part%20of%20the%20yield%20curve%2C%26quot%3B%20Zaccarelli%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20that%20do%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20stocks%20in%20a%20high-rate%20environment%2C%20look%20for%20quality%2C%20Sl%C3%B8k%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20interest%20rates%20are%20higher%20for%20longer%2C%20companies%20with%20earnings%20tend%20to%20outperform%20because%20companies%20with%20earnings%20are%20able%20to%20pay%20higher%20debt%20servicing%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20Sl%C3%B8k%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDividend-paying%20stocks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20are%20also%20a%20good%20investment%20in%20times%20like%20these%2C%20according%20to%20Rosner.%20Companies%20that%20pay%20dividends%20are%20typically%20well-established%2C%20profitable%2C%20and%20have%20stable%20cash%20flows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinancials%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eare%20positioned%20to%20do%20well%2C%20too%2C%20said%20Chris%20Brigati%2C%20chief%20investment%20officer%20at%20investment%20firm%20SWBC.%20That's%20because%20he%20expects%20the%20yield%20curve%20to%20continue%20steepening%20as%20long-term%20Treasury%20rates%20creep%20higher.%20Banks%20borrow%20at%20the%20short-term%20rate%20and%20lend%20at%20the%20long-term%20rate%2C%20and%20higher%20interest%20rates%20will%20increase%20the%20amount%20banks%20earn%20on%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnergy%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20another%20sector%20that'll%20benefit%20from%20higher%20rates%2C%20both%20Brigati%20and%20Zaccarelli%20said.%20Energy%20and%20other%20commodities%20have%20historically%20performed%20well%20in%20higher%20rate%20and%20inflationary%20environments%2C%20according%20to%20Zaccarelli.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20in%20a%20business%20where%20you're%20selling%20a%20commodity%20and%20you%20can%20continue%20to%20provide%20that%20service%20or%20good%20at%20a%20continually%20higher%20price%20and%20consumers%20are%20forced%20to%20buy%20it%20at%20any%20price%2C%20then%20you're%20typically%20more%20insulated%20from%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Zaccarelli%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20stay%20away%20from%20utilities%2C%20Zaccarelli%20warned%2C%20as%20the%20sector%20is%20inflation-sensitive.%20Utilities%20companies%20are%20also%20susceptible%20to%20interest-rate%20risk%20due%20to%20their%20capital-extensive%20business%20models%20and%20high%20debt%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20can%20get%20exposure%20to%20these%20trades%20through%20funds%20like%20the%20iShares%201-3%20Year%20Treasury%20Bond%20ETF%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fishares-1-3-year-treasury-bond-etf-us4642874576%3FmiRedirects%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESHY%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20the%20Financial%20Select%20Sector%20SPDR%20Fund%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fthe-financial-select-sector-spdr-fund-us81369y6059%3FmiRedirects%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EXLF%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20the%20Vanguard%20Energy%20ETF%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fvanguard-energy-index-fund-etf-shares-us92204a3068%3FmiRedirects%3D2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVDE%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20and%20the%20SPDR%20Portfolio%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20High%20Dividend%20ETF%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fspdr-portfolio-sp-500-high-dividend-etf-us78468r7888%3FmiRedirects%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESPYD%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-to-invest-trades-higher-for-longer-interest-rates-inflation-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739787302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679970b1196626c409859219%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22origi