Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20drone%20unit%20in%20Ukraine%20said%20it%20destroyed%20three%20prized%20Russian%20air%20defense%20systems%20in%20a%20single%20day.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20posted%20clips%20of%20drone%20attacks%2C%20saying%20it%20hit%20a%20Tor-M2%2C%20a%20Buk-M2%2C%20and%20a%20Buk-M3.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20its%20post%20on%20Saturday%2C%20the%20unit%20also%20highlighted%20that%20the%20drones%20were%20funded%20by%20civilians.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drone%20unit%20of%20a%20Ukrainian%20brigade%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%20said%20it%20destroyed%20three%20advanced%20Russian%20air%20defense%20systems%20in%20a%20single%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ronin%20company%20of%20the%2065th%20Mechanized%20Rifle%20Brigade%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.me%2FRonins44_65%2F453%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eposted%20footage%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20first-person%20view%20drone%20attacks%20on%20Saturday%2C%20saying%20it%20took%20out%20a%20Tor-M2%2C%20a%20Buk-M2%2C%20and%20a%20Buk-M3.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20are%20some%20of%20Moscow's%20most%20prized%20mobile%20surface-to-air%20missile%20systems%2C%20with%20the%20Tor-M2%20lauded%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.com%2Fdefense%2F1580769%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20state%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcutting-edge%26quot%3B%20weapon%20that%20can%20counter%20drone%20swarms%20on%20the%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20range%20of%20about%207.5%20miles%2C%20the%20Tor-M2%20is%20designed%20to%20engage%20up%20to%2048%20targets%20at%20once%20at%20low%20to%20medium%20altitudes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Buk-M3%20is%20also%20one%20of%20Russia's%20newest%20air%20defenses.%20Russian%20state%20media%20outlet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.com%2Fdefense%2F1580769%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETASS%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecompared%20it%20in%202016%20to%20the%20Medium%20Extended%20Air%20Defense%20System%2C%20a%20Western-made%20system%20meant%