urope%20needs%20to%20up%20our%20defense%20spending%20very%20fast%20and%20very%20significantly%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stand%20on%20equal%20footing%20with%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGermany's%20defense%20minister%2C%20Boris%20Pistorius%2C%20also%20addressed%20the%20issue%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20critics%20are%20right%20that%20we%20have%20to%20do%20more%20and%20that%20we%20did%20too%20little%20in%20the%20years%20before%2C%20much%20too%20little.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Rutte%2C%20NATO's%20Secretary%20General%2C%20has%20also%20frequently%20called%20on%20European%20members%20of%20the%20alliance%20to%20boost%20military%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20in%20Munich%2C%20he%20said%20the%20US%20was%20%26quot%3Bright%26quot%3B%20to%20think%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20to%20step%20up%2C%20we%20have%20to%20spend%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20both%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20were%20%26quot%3Bnot%20producing%20nearly%20enough%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20Russia%20produces%20more%20ammunition%20in%20three%20months%20than%20NATO%20does%20in%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Vice%20President%20JD%20Vance%2C%20also%20appearing%20in%20Munich%2C%20seemed%20unmoved%20by%20Europe's%20pledges%2C%20and%20used%20his%20speech%20to%20attack%20what%20he%20called%20free%20speech%20violations%20in%20Europe.%20Vance%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bgreat%26quot%3B%20that%20Europe%20was%20planning%20to%20boost%20defense%20spending%20but%20that%20he%20was%20more%20worried%20about%20the%20threat%20to%20Europe%20from%20%26quot%3Bwithin%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20part%2C%20Trump%20has%20long%20called%20for%20Europe%20to%20spend%20more%20on%20defense%2C%20threatening%20to%20leave%20NATO%20if%20that%20did%20not%20happen%20and%20even%20suggesting%20before%20he%20was%20re-elected%20that%20he%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-trump-nato-russia-comments-appalling-unhinged-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallow%20Russia%20to%20attack%20NATO%20members%20that%20don't%20spend%20enough%20on%20defense%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20countries%20have%20already%20taken%20big%20steps%20toward%20boosting%20spending.%20In%202024%2C%20Poland%20led%20the%20alliance%20in%20defense%20spending%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20GDP%2C%20with%20Warsaw%20investing%20more%20than%204%25%20of%20its%20economic%20output%20in%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELithuania%20and%20Estonia%20have%20also%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-member-beside-russia-thrilled-trump-wants-more-defense-spending-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epledged%20to%20increase%20their%20own%20defense%20spending%20to%205%25%20of%20GDP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20that%20while%20they%20agreed%20with%20Trump's%20demands%2C%20they%20were%20not%20taking%20that%20step%20solely%20because%20of%20the%20president%20but%20because%20of%20Russia's%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20future%20of%20the%20US-Europe%20alliance%20appears%20at%20risk%20over%20more%20than%20just%20defense%20spending.%20Trump's%20team%20in%20recent%20days%20suggested%20Europe%20could%20be%20sidelined%20in%20negotiations%20between%20Russia%20and%20the%20US%20on%20Ukraine%20and%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bunrealistic%26quot%3B%20that%20Ukraine%20could%20get%20back%20all%20territory%20occupied%20by%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20rising%20tensions%2C%20many%20leaders%20said%20in%20Munich%20that%20there%20were%20still%20opportunities%20to%20keep%20working%20with%20the%20US%20to%20combat%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKristr%C3%BAn%20Mj%C3%B6ll%20Frostad%C3%B3ttir%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20Iceland%2C%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20easy%20to%20become%20very%20negative%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20US-Europe%20relationship%20and%20called%20the%20situation%20%26quot%3Buncomfortable%26quot%3B%20as%20Ukraine's%20sovereignty%20is%20at%20stake.%20But%20%26quot%3Bthat%20doesn't%20mean%20relations%20with%20the%20US%20have%20to%20be%20bad%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C5%A0akalien%C4%97%20added%20that%20while%20Trump%20had%20%26quot%3Bunique%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bunexpected%26quot%3B%20negotiating%20tactics%2C%20that%20wasn't%20necessarily%20a%20negative%20thing%20as%20%26quot%3Bplaying%20by%20the%20rules%20does%20not%20work%20with%20Russia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20other%20European%20officials%20said%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20the%20US%20also%20needs%20Europe%20and%20its%20capabilities%20as%20an%20ally%2C%20she%20went%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feurope-weapon-making-issue-highlighted-ukraine-being-faster-denmark-pm-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739719221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b1d5a0eb4be2fff9a4ce59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feurope-weapon-making-issue-highlighted-ukraine-being-faster-denmark-pm-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Danish%20Prime%20Minister%20Mette%20Frederiksen%20warned%20Saturday%20that%20Europe%20must%20ramp%20up%20production%20efforts%20going%20forward.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbaker%40insider.com%20(Sin%C3%A9ad%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A476%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feurope-weapon-making-issue-highlighted-ukraine-being-faster-denmark-pm-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22South%20Korean%20actress%20Kim%20Sae-ron%2C%2024%2C%20found%20dead%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739719047000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F6fd4%2Flive%2F05338e70-ec6d-11ef-a319-fb4e7360c4ec.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc626p25egddo%230%22%2C%22summary%2